parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel bearing can cause the wheel to wobble or shake violently, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or jerking motion in the front wheel
wheel bearing coming apart
missing ball bearings
vibration or shaking of the handlebars
wobbling or shaking of the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose spokes on wire wheels can cause the handlebars to vibrate or shake violently, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Vibration or shaking of the handlebars
wobbling or shaking of the front end
loose spokes on wire wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The wobbling or shaking of the steering forks can cause loss of control and potential accidents, especially when decelerating or at certain speeds.
symptoms: Wobbling or shaking of the steering forks
handlebars shaking back and forth
violent shaking of the front end
loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the brakes to malfunction or completely disable, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.

brake lever seized or frozen
inability to slow or stop the vehicle
brake lever stuck in an open position
sudden loss of brake function.

symptoms: Brake lever seized or frozen
inability to slow or stop the vehicle

sudden loss of brake function.

inability to slow or stop the vehicle.
